humanMachineDialogue.text: The report states that there are metastases in 2 out of 14 lymph nodes (2/14) in the left breast with axillary contents. This corresponds to the N1 stage based on New Rule 12, which indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes.

humanMachineDialogue.text: The N stage for a cancer patient is determined by the presence and extent of cancer in the lymph nodes. In this report, the patient has metastatic carcinoma in one of one non-sentinel lymph node examined in the left axilla (1/1), with extranodal extension. This corresponds to an N1 stage. The specific N1 subcategory is not provided in the report, so we can only determine the main N1 stage.
